ğŸ§© 1ï¸âƒ£ What is a LinkedList?

In simple words:

A LinkedList is a data structure where elements (called nodes)
are connected using links (pointers) instead of being stored in a
continuous block of memory like an array.

| Feature           | Array                      | LinkedList                      |
| ----------------- | -------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| **Storage**       | Continuous memory          | Non-continuous (nodes linked)   |
| **Access speed**  | Fast (index-based)         | Slow (traverse from start)      |
| **Insert/Delete** | Expensive (shift elements) | Easy (change links only)        |
| **Memory usage**  | Less (only data)           | More (data + link to next node) |


class Node{
    int data;  // data part
    Node next; // link to next node

    Node(int data){
        this.data = data;
        this.next = null;
    }
}

ğŸ§© 1ï¸âƒ£ â€” Why class Node?
=> LinkedList is a collection of nodes.
=> Each node has 2 things
    1. Data (value) â€” jo actual element store karta hai
    2. Next (link/reference) â€” jo next node ka address store karta hai

ğŸ§  Isliye hume ek custom data type banana padta hai jisme dono cheeze ho.

